comments: Thomas (BKN) closes out the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with George's (LAC) slightly extended right foot after the release.

In an effort to find his man and box out, Claxton (BKN) brings his left arm backward and makes marginal contact to Westbrook's (LAC) shoulder/neck area during the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Johnson (BKN) makes incidental arm contact with Westbrook (LAC) as they each pursue the rebound.
Finney-Smith (BKN) cleanly dislodges the ball away from Leonard (LAC) during the inbound.
Johnson (BKN) steps out of bounds while in possession of the ball.
Leonard (LAC) grasps and then quickly releases Finney-Smith's (BKN) left arm during the drive.
Finney-Smith's (BKN) brushes Leonard's (LAC) front and makes marginal contact while defending the play in the corner.
Finney-Smith (BKN) brings his left forearm toward Leonard's (LAC) left side and marginal contact occurs as Leonard is losing his balance in pursuit of the loose ball.
Leonard (LAC) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Claxton (BKN) establishes himself in George's (LAC) path and does not deliver illegal contact as he sets the screen.
Dinwiddie (BKN) brings his forearm toward Harden's (LAC) side and marginal contact occurs as Harden accelerates during the drive.
Westbrook (LAC) jumps forward slightly prior to marginal contact occurring with Bridges' (BKN) slightly extended off-arm during the driving shot attempt.
George (LAC) slightly extends toward Claxton (BKN) when marginal body contact occurs as they each attempt to establish rebounding position.
Harden (LAC) turns slightly as marginal contact occurs with Thomas' (BKN) side prior to Thomas' gather.
George (LAC) maintains verticality and absorbs the incidental contact that occurs during Thomas' (BKN) driving shot attempt.
Thomas (BKN) brings his right hand toward Leonard's (LAC) right leg and marginal contact occurs after the release of Leonard's jump shot attempt.
Westbrook (LAC) drifts forward slightly prior to marginal contact occurring with Thomas' (BKN) slightly extended off-arm during the driving shot attempt.
Mann (LAC) and Claxton (BKN) each make clean contact with the ball as simultaneous incidental contact occurs during the rebound.
